label: LABEL
definition: A definition
type: TYPE

label: reason for lack of data item
definition: An information content entity that provides an explanation why a data item is not provided.
example of usage: cannot be assessed, not applicable, unknown

label: cannot be assessed determination
definition: A reason for lack of data item that is the negative output of a determination if assay will provide reliable results.
parent class: reason for lack of data item

label: determination if assay will provide reliable results
definition: A planned process that is used to assess whether an assay will provide reliable results based on the conditions or qualities of the inputs, devices, and other participants of the assay.

label: GX
definition: A cannot be assessed determination for histologic tumor grade.
example of usage: AJCC 7th edition GX: cannot be assessed.

label: pTX
definition: A cannot be assessed determination for pathologic primary tumor staging.
example of usage: AJCC 7th edition pTX: cannot be assessed.

label: pNX
definition: A cannot be assessed determination of pathologic staging of lymph nodes.
example of usage: AJCC 7th edition pNX: cannot be assessed.

label: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.

label: G1: Well differentiated
definition: A histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor cells and the organization of the tumor tissue appear close to normal.
type: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition

label: G2: Moderately differentiated
definition: A histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor cells are moderately differentiated and reflect an intermediate grade.
type: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition

label: G3: Poorly differentiated
definition: A histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor cells are poorly differentiated and do not look like normal cells and tissue.
type: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition

label: G4: Undifferentiated
definition: A histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor cells are undifferentiated and do not look like normal cells and tissue.
type: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition

label: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System.

label: G1 (Fuhrman)
definition: A histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System indicating that nuclei are round, uniform, approximately 10um and that nucleoli are inconspicuous or absent.
type: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System

label: G2 (Fuhrman)
definition: A histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System indicating that nuclei are slightly irregular, approximately 15um and nucleoli are evident.
type: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System

label: G3 (Fuhrman)
definition: A histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System indicating that nuclei are very irregular, approximately 20um and nucleoli large and prominent.
type: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System

label: G4 (Fuhrman)
definition: A histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System indicating that nuclei arei bizarre and multilobulated, 20um or greater and nucleoli are prominent and chromatin clumped.
type: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System

label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a ovarian tumor.

label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a two-tier histological classification of tumors.

label: Low grade ovarian tumor
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system indicating that the tumor is low grade.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system

label: High grade ovarian tumor
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system indicating that the tumor is high grade.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system

label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a histological classification by the World Health Organization (WHO).

label: G1 (WHO)
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization indicating that the tumor is well differentiated.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization

label: G2 (WHO)
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization indicating that the tumor is moderately differentiated.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization

label: G3 (WHO)
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization indicating that the tumor is poorly differentiated.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization

label: G4 (WHO)
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization indicating that the tumor is undifferentiated.
type: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization

label: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pT: Pathologic spread colorectal primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: pT0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pTis (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating carcinoma in situ (intraepithelial or invasion of lamina propria).
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades submucosa.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades muscularis propria.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades subserosa or into non-peritionealized pericolic or perirectal tissues.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT4a (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor perforates visceral peritoneum.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT4b (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor directly invades other organs or structures.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pT: Pathologic spread lung primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: pT0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pTis (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating carcinoma in situ.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus).
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 2 cm or less in greatest dimension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 2 cm but not more than 3 cm in greatest dimension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 3 cm but not more than 7 cm or the tumor has any of the following features: involves main bronchus, 2 cm or more distal to the carina, invades visceral pleura, associated with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis that extends to the hilar region but does not involve the entire lung.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2a (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 3 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2b (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 5 cm but not more than 7 cm in greatest dimension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm or one that directly invades any of: parietal pleura, chest wall (including superior sulcus tumors), diaphragm, phrenic nerve, mediastinal pleura, parietal pericardiu or the tumor is in the main bronchus less than 2 cm distal to the carina but without  involvement of the carina or there is associated atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis of the entire lung or there is separate tumor nodule(s) in the same lobe as the primary.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT4 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor of any size that invades any of the following: mediastinum, heart, great vessels, trachea, recurrent laryngeal nerve, esophagus, vertebral body, carina or there is separate tumor nodule(s) in a different ipsilateral lobe to that of the primary.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pT: Pathologic spread kidney primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: pT0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 7 cm or less in greatest dimension and limited to the kidney.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 4 cm or less.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 4 cm but not more than 7 cm.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm in greatest dimension and limited to the kidney.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm but not more than 10 cm.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 10 cm and limited to the kidney.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor extends into major veins or perinephric tissues but not into the ipsilateral adrenal gland and not beyond the Gerota fascia.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into the renal vein or its segmental (muscle containing) branches, or the tumor invades perirenal and/or renal sinus fat (peripelvic) fat but not beyond Gerota fascia.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into vena cava below diaphragm.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3c (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into vena cava above the diaphragm or Invades the wall of the vena cava.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT4 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades beyond Gerota fascia (including contiguous extension into the ipsilateral adrenal gland).
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pT: Pathologic spread ovarian primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: pT0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to the ovaries (one or both).
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to one ovary; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to both ovaries; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT1c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to one or both ovaries with capsule ruptured, tumor on ovarian surface, or malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor involves one or both ovaries with pelvic extension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has extension and/or implants on uterus and/or tube(s) and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has extension to other pelvic tissues and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT2c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has pelvic extension with malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor involves one or both ovaries with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis outside the pelvis and/or regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has microscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has macroscopic peritoneal, metastatasis beyond pelvis, 2 cm or less in greatest dimension.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pT3c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis, more than 2 cm in greatest dimension and/or regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pN: Pathologic spread colon lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label: pN0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating no regional lymph node metastsis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 1 regional lymph node.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 2-3 regional lymph nodes.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1c (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating tumor deposit(s), i.e., satellites in the subserosa, or in non-peritonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissue without regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN2 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 4 or more regional lymph nodes.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN2a (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 4 to 6 regional lymph nodes.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN2b (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 7 or more regional lymph nodes.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pN: Pathologic spread colon lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label: pN0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating no regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes and intrapulmonary nodes, including involvement by direct extension.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN2 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in ipsilateral mediastinal and/or subcarinal lymph node(s).
type: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN3 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in contralateral mediastinal, contralateral hilar, ipsilateral or contralateral scalene, or supraclavicular lymph node(s).
type: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pN: Pathologic spread kidney lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label: pN0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
alternative term: pN: Pathologic spread ovarian lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label: pN0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pN1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is regional lymph node metastasis.
type: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colon cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: cM0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are no symptoms or signs of distant metastasis.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is clinical evidence of distant metastases by history, physical examination, imaging studies, or invasive procedures, but without microscopic evidence of the presumed distant metastases.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is confined to one organ based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is in more than one organ or the peritoneum based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is microscopic evidence confirming distant metastatic disease.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is confined to one organ and histologically confirmed.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is in more than one organ or the peritoneum and histologically confirmed.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: cM0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are distant metastases based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is based on clinical assessment and a separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules OR malignant pleural or pericardial effusion.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is histologically confirmed and a separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules OR malignant pleural or pericardial effusion.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed and associated with distant lymph nodes or carcinomatosis.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: cM0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are distant metastases based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a  pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label: cM0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: cM1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is distant metastasis except peritoneal metastasis based on clinical assessment.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: pM1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is distant metastasis except peritoneal metastasis that is histologically confirmed.
type: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

label: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

label: Occult Carcinoma (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating a small carcinoma, either asymptomatic or giving rise to metastases without symptoms due to the primary carcinoma.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage 0 (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating a carcinoma in situ (or melanoma in situ for melanoma of the skin or germ cell neoplasia in situ for testicular germ cell tumors) and generally is considered to have no metastatic potential.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage I (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers that are smaller or less deeply invasive without regional disease or nodes.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIB and IIC.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIA and IIC.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIC (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIA and IIB.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIIA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIB and IIIC.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIIB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIA and IIIC.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IIIC (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIA and IIIB.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IVA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers in patients who present with distant metastases at diagnosis and with differing characteristics from IVB.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: Stage IVB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers in patients who present with distant metastases at diagnosis and with differing characteristics from IVA.
type: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification
definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a gynecologic cancer according to the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging systems.

label: Stage IA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating invasive carcinoma which can be diagnosed only by microscopy, with deepest invasion <5 mm and the largest extension <7 mm.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IA1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating measured stromal invasion of <3.0 mm in depth and extension of <7.0 mm.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IA2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating measured stromal invasion of >3.0 mm and not >5.0 mm with an extension of not >7.0 mm.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesions limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IB1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesion limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA <4.0 cm in greatest dimension.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IB2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesion limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA >4.0 cm in greatest dimension.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIA1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion and clinically visible lesion <4.0 cm in greatest dimension.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIA2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion and clinically visible lesion >4.0 cm in greatest dimension.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina with obvious parametrial invasion.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIIA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating tumour involves lower third of the vagina, with no extension to the pelvic wall.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IIIB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating extension to the pelvic wall and/or hydronephrosis or non-functioning kidney.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IVA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating spread of the growth to adjacent organs.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: Stage IVB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating spread to distant organs.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification
alternative term: Pathologic Tumor Stage Grouping for ovarian cancer (FIGO)
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the FIGO classification system.

label: Stage 1 (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T1, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 1A (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T1a, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 1B (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T1b, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 1C (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T1c, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 2 (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T2, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 2A (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T2a, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 2B (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T2b, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 2C (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T2c, N0, and M0.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 3 (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of (T3, N0, and M0) or (T3,3a,3b, NX, and M0).
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 3A (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T3a, N0, and M0 .
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 3B (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T3b, N0, and M0 .
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 3C (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of (T3c, N0,X and M0) or (any T, N1 and M0).
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage 4 (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of any T, any N, and M1.
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: Stage Unknown (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of (T0, N0, and M0) or (T1,1a-1c,2,2a-2c, NX, and M0) or (TX, N0,X, M0).
type: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

label: performance status value specification
definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).

label: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification
definition: A performance status value specification designed by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group to assess disease progression and its affect on the daily living abilities of the patient.

label: 3: symptomatic in bed more than 50% of the day but not bed ridden
definition: An Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification indicating a patient is symptomatic and in bed for more than 50% of the day but is not bed ridden.
type: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

label: 2: symptomatic but in bed less than 50% of the day
definition: An Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification indicating a patient is symptomatic but is in bed for less than 50% of the day.
type: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

label: 4: bed ridden
definition: An Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification indicating a patient is symptomatic and is bed ridden.
type: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

label: 0: asymptomatic
definition: An Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification indicating a patient is asymptomatic.
type: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

label: 1: symptomatic but fully ambulatory
definition: An Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification indicating a patient is symptomatic but is fully ambulatory.
type: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

label: Karnofsky score vaue specification
definition: A performance status value specification designed for classifying patients 16 years of age or older by their functional impairment.

label: 100: asymptomatic
definition: A Karnofsky score vaue specification indicating that a patient is asymptomatic.
type: Karnofsky score vaue specification

label: 80-90: symptomatic but fully ambulatory
definition: A Karnofsky score vaue specification indicating that a patient is symptomatic but fully ambulatory.
type: Karnofsky score vaue specification

label: 60-70: symptomatic but in bed less than 50% of the day
definition: A Karnofsky score vaue specification indicating that a patient is symptomatic but in bed less than 50% of the day.
type: Karnofsky score vaue specification

label: 40-50: symptomatic, in bed more than 50% of the day, but not bed ridden
definition: A Karnofsky score vaue specification indicating that a patient is symptomatic, in bed more than 50% of the day, but not bed ridden.
type: Karnofsky score vaue specification

label: medication time value specification
definition: A scalar value specification that specifies the point in time that a human participant under investigation self-administers a medication material

label: medication dose value specification
definition: A scalar value specification that specifies the value of the quantity of a material entity administered to an organism as a treatment

label: hypertension grade
definition: A categorical value specification that indicates the severity of hypertension.
